00:33:07,570 --> 00:33:11,365
Remember, Kirsten, we had this scene
of you dancing in the window.

457
00:33:11,532 --> 00:33:13,200
That was too provocative.

458
00:33:13,367 --> 00:33:17,246
Initially this took place
over a number of days.

459
00:33:17,413 --> 00:33:19,415
So at one point in the scene...

460
00:33:19,582 --> 00:33:23,252
...Peter looks out his window
and Mary Jane's dancing.

461
00:33:23,419 --> 00:33:25,921
I was first dancing in my underwear.

462
00:33:26,088 --> 00:33:29,091
- Then in a leopard thong. Not really.
- We covered you up.

463
00:33:29,300 --> 00:33:32,595
Then I wore pajama pants
because it was a little too much.

464
00:33:32,803 --> 00:33:37,141
- Now I see the spider webs, kind of.
- See the spider webs?

465
00:33:38,309 --> 00:33:41,103
- I love this, when he's lying.
- This is hilarious.

466
00:33:41,270 --> 00:33:44,565
"Okay, thanks." Like such a little boy.
So cute.

467
00:33:44,732 --> 00:33:46,233
- Tobey ad-libbed.
- Cute.

468
00:33:46,400 --> 00:33:49,111
That came out of the scene with her.

469
00:33:49,278 --> 00:33:53,699
- I love that. I love the webs.
- Yeah. That looks cool.

470
00:33:55,201 --> 00:33:57,369
Meanwhile...

471
00:34:13,135 --> 00:34:16,472
Something's bothering him. Maybe
he's too embarrassed to tell me.

472
00:34:16,639 --> 00:34:19,350
Maybe I'm too embarrassed
to ask him.

473
00:34:20,142 --> 00:34:22,144
I just don't know anymore.

474
00:34:22,603 --> 00:34:25,147
I'm going to the library.
See you later.

475
00:34:25,356 --> 00:34:28,734
- Wait, Pete. I'll drive you there, buddy.
- I'll take the train.

476
00:34:28,901 --> 00:34:30,653
No, I need the exercise.
Go on. Go, go.

477
00:34:30,861 --> 00:34:34,990
He needs the exercise.
That's a funny line.

478
00:34:38,327 --> 00:34:40,621
There's the car, Sam.

479
00:34:43,165 --> 00:34:47,127
It's an 88 Oldsmobile Delta.
1973?

480
00:34:47,294 --> 00:34:51,173
It's a, yeah, 1973 Delta 88 Oldsmobile.

481
00:34:51,423 --> 00:34:53,676
Kids, it's currently for sale.

482
00:34:53,884 --> 00:34:57,805
If you'd like to own a piece of
the Spider-Man movie, just contact me.

483
00:34:57,972 --> 00:35:00,307
There's a little problem
with the radiator.

484
00:35:00,474 --> 00:35:03,352
But otherwise I would recommend it
to compliment...

485
00:35:03,519 --> 00:35:08,023
...any connoisseur's
motion-picture-prop movie collection.

486
00:35:08,190 --> 00:35:10,943
No collection is complete without it.

487
00:35:11,402 --> 00:35:14,363
No, you're not supposed
to run away, but...

488
00:35:14,530 --> 00:35:19,118
Pete, you're changing. I went through
exactly the same thing at your age.

489
00:35:19,326 --> 00:35:21,328
No, not exactly.

490
00:35:21,662 --> 00:35:25,374
Peter, these are the years
when a man changes...

491
00:35:25,541 --> 00:35:29,545
...into the man he's gonna become
the rest of his life.

492
00:35:29,712 --> 00:35:32,840
Just be careful who you change into.

493
00:35:34,383 --> 00:35:38,887
This guy Flash Thompson,
he probably deserved what happened.

494
00:35:39,346 --> 00:35:41,390
Cliff made this scene work...

495
00:35:41,557 --> 00:35:45,477
...beautifully. It's one of my favorite
scenes in the picture.

496
00:35:45,644 --> 00:35:50,733
Remember, with great power
comes great responsibility.

497
00:35:51,358 --> 00:35:56,363
Are you afraid I'll become a criminal?
Quit worrying about me, okay?

498
00:35:56,530 --> 00:35:58,741
Something's different.
I'll figure it out.

499
00:35:58,907 --> 00:36:05,331
I kept Cliff up till like 2 in morning the
previous night, recutting this scene.

500
00:36:05,497 --> 00:36:08,083
Trying to make the dialogue play,
rewriting it.

501
00:36:08,250 --> 00:36:11,253
He was exhausted
because it was a 6 a.m. call.

502
00:36:11,462 --> 00:36:14,340
So he had three and a half hours
of sleep.

503
00:36:14,506 --> 00:36:17,551
Yeah, he did a great job that night.

504
00:36:17,718 --> 00:36:23,515
I love that Danny played the theme here
too. It's such an interesting impulse.

505
00:36:24,224 --> 00:36:28,896
He had two themes going,
Peter's theme and Spider-Man's theme.

506
00:36:29,063 --> 00:36:34,276
And they would each derive from
the other. But I love that he played...

507
00:36:34,443 --> 00:36:36,904
...that right there.

508
00:36:46,413 --> 00:36:47,873
This was pretty funny.

509
00:36:48,040 --> 00:36:54,755
That's Bone Saw. That's Randy Savage,
and he's, obviously, a wrestler.

510
00:36:55,297 --> 00:37:00,260
And when he came to audition for us,
I just fell in love with his voice.

511
00:37:00,427 --> 00:37:03,555
Like, amazing, that voice.

512
00:37:07,267 --> 00:37:12,064
Remember when Randy Savage
met with you for the first time on this?

513
00:37:12,231 --> 00:37:14,608
I can't remember our first meeting.

514
00:37:14,817 --> 00:37:17,027
You were asking him
what type of moves...

515
00:37:17,194 --> 00:37:19,321
...he thought
would be good on-screen.

516
00:37:19,488 --> 00:37:23,200
I'll never forget, he grabbed
Ian Bryce, our producer...

517
00:37:23,367 --> 00:37:27,079
...his head, shoved them between his
legs, demonstrated a pile driver on Ian.

518
00:37:27,246 --> 00:37:29,415
I thought he was gonna kill Ian.

519
00:37:29,581 --> 00:37:34,795
Ian's face was turning red,
and Randy just kept working him over.

520
00:37:35,045 --> 00:37:36,672
I felt so sorry for Ian.

521
00:37:36,839 --> 00:37:39,299
There's my buddy, Bruce Campbell.

522
00:37:39,508 --> 00:37:42,594
I love the fact that he would
do this for me. Be in this picture.

523
00:37:42,761 --> 00:37:45,305
I only wish I could've punished him
in some way.

524
00:37:45,472 --> 00:37:48,767
The audience enjoys Bruce's
performances in films relative to...

525
00:37:48,934 --> 00:37:53,981
...the amount of punishment
he endures in the picture.

526
00:37:54,148 --> 00:37:57,443
- Remember that young lady's name?
- Octavia Spencer.

527
00:37:57,609 --> 00:37:59,862
The check-in lady.
Is that who you're asking?

528
00:38:00,028 --> 00:38:04,783
- Yeah, she did a great job.
- She was Francine Maisler's assistant.

529
00:38:04,950 --> 00:38:08,871
Sometimes. She comes in and
helps. She did a really good job for us.

530
00:38:09,079 --> 00:38:11,832
We had footage of those women
beating up that wrestler.

531
00:38:11,999 --> 00:38:15,461
Kicking him in the face and stomach
once he was down.

532
00:38:15,669 --> 00:38:19,298
But we just didn't have time
to incorporate everything in the picture.

533
00:38:19,465 --> 00:38:24,636
I love Bruce's Cadillac medallion
that they put on him.

534
00:38:24,803 --> 00:38:28,056
James Acheson gave him. Yes.

535
00:38:30,559 --> 00:38:35,230
If he can withstand just three minutes
in the cage with Bone Saw McGraw...

536
00:38:35,522 --> 00:38:39,902
...the sum of $3000 will be paid to...

537
00:38:40,736 --> 00:38:43,739
- What's your name, kid?
- The Human Spider.

538
00:38:44,364 --> 00:38:46,658
That's it? That's the best you got?

539
00:38:46,825 --> 00:38:49,411
Bruce is so great.

540
00:38:51,663 --> 00:38:55,250
You probably won't admit to it,
but if you look closely...

541
00:38:55,417 --> 00:39:00,547
...I think I remember who pushed
Spider-Man onto the platform that day.

542
00:39:00,839 --> 00:39:03,425
- I think that's Sam Raimi.
- Just the hand.

543
00:39:03,634 --> 00:39:05,761
I love shoving Spider-Man around.

544
00:39:05,928 --> 00:39:08,764
- No, he got my name wrong.
- Get out there, you moron.

545
00:39:09,223 --> 00:39:13,018
That was our PA, Rhys, who shoved
him out, but that was your hand.

546
00:39:13,185 --> 00:39:16,688
I think I remember who was throwing
the popcorn at Tobey here as well.

547
00:39:16,855 --> 00:39:18,732
- How dare you?
- Yeah, well...

548
00:39:20,067 --> 00:39:21,902
You're not as nice
as everybody says.

549
00:39:22,069 --> 00:39:24,112
Somebody's gotta tell
the truth someday.

550
00:39:24,279 --> 00:39:28,242
- It was a pleasure working with you.
- Yeah. Thank you, sir.

551
00:39:28,951 --> 00:39:30,619
Oh, my legs.

552
00:39:30,786 --> 00:39:33,413
Oh, God. I can't feel my legs.

553
00:39:33,789 --> 00:39:38,043
That's something...
That line came from a real story.

554
00:39:38,210 --> 00:39:42,256
Rob Taperd once was driving from
Detroit, and he had just...

555
00:39:42,422 --> 00:39:44,758
My partner, good friend...

556
00:39:44,925 --> 00:39:48,053
...and he was going past
an automobile accident...

557
00:39:48,220 --> 00:39:52,099
...and they were pulling some guy out,
and that was what he was screaming:

558
00:39:52,266 --> 00:39:55,310
"My legs! Oh, God,
I can't feel my legs."

559
00:39:55,477 --> 00:39:57,980
- As horrible as it was...
- How twisted.

560
00:39:58,188 --> 00:40:00,816
That's why it's in the picture.

561
00:40:00,983 --> 00:40:05,404
Really wanted to give Peter Parker
a taste of what was to come.

562
00:40:05,571 --> 00:40:08,490
This is some kind of mistake.
I didn't sign up for a cage match!

563
00:40:09,700 --> 00:40:12,327
Unlock the thing! Take the chain off!

564
00:40:12,494 --> 00:40:17,165
Mark Andrews, our storyboard artist,
contributed an incredible amount...

565
00:40:17,332 --> 00:40:22,087
...to this whole fight scene. A lot
of the ideas in this scene are his...

566
00:40:22,337 --> 00:40:27,467
...and it's guided by his brilliance
and his great storyboarding.

567
00:40:28,635 --> 00:40:31,471
- Remember Mark?
- Oh, yeah. Great guy. He's an animal.

568
00:40:31,638 --> 00:40:36,602
He could just crank those out.
He had such great ideas too.

569
00:40:38,270 --> 00:40:42,482
A lot of these fighting moves were
developed by Jeff Habberstad...

570
00:40:42,983 --> 00:40:48,155
...and others by Chris, our stuntman.

571
00:40:48,322 --> 00:40:52,117
Chris Daniels did a lot of great work.
Great spidey-pose reference.

572
00:40:52,284 --> 00:40:56,038
He did a lot of homework.
He really knows his Spider-Man poses.

573
00:40:56,246 --> 00:40:59,291
Some of the ideas came
from watching those wrestling videos.

574
00:40:59,499 --> 00:41:03,045
Like beating him up with the chair.

575
00:41:03,253 --> 00:41:05,380
Randy had a lot of input on all this.

576
00:41:05,547 --> 00:41:08,675
Wasn't this one of the first sequences
we filmed...

577
00:41:08,884 --> 00:41:11,011
...with the wrestling arena?

578
00:41:11,219 --> 00:41:13,889
Yes, it was. I remember they had a big
press conference...

579
00:41:14,139 --> 00:41:16,808
- ...and it took place in this arena.
- Yeah.

580
00:41:17,017 --> 00:41:18,894
Right, Ian scheduled it early.

581
00:41:19,061 --> 00:41:23,982
We had to film it to make way for the
balcony sequence in Times Square.

582
00:41:24,191 --> 00:41:27,986
It was filmed on the same stage.
We had to film here and get out.

583
00:41:28,153 --> 00:41:32,157
All of those guys in the crowd did
an incredible job, all the extras.

584
00:41:32,324 --> 00:41:36,495
They put so much energy
into the screaming and the jumping.

585
00:41:36,662 --> 00:41:39,581
I could tell they loved Spider-Man.
That's why they were there.

586
00:41:39,790 --> 00:41:41,833
We got a better performances...

587
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:45,671
...than usual
because they're such fans of the comic.

588
00:41:45,837 --> 00:41:50,884
Cash Oshman was the extras casting
director and he did a good job...

589
00:41:51,051 --> 00:41:52,928
...of giving us a lot of great people.

590
00:41:53,095 --> 00:41:56,098
A hundred bucks?
The ad said $3000.

591
00:41:56,306 --> 00:42:00,394
I like Neil's set in this room
and the hallway, and the sound job.

592
00:42:00,560 --> 00:42:07,025
They work to tell the story that this is
some subterranean area of the arena.

593
00:42:07,693 --> 00:42:10,112
Which is a hard thing to communicate.

594
00:42:10,278 --> 00:42:12,989
The promoter is played
by Larry Joshua...

595
00:42:13,156 --> 00:42:15,742
...one of my favorite character actors.

596
00:42:17,452 --> 00:42:23,291
This is such a pivotal scene, and so
much right out of the comic book...

597
00:42:23,458 --> 00:42:28,213
...and something we felt
we had to really do in a way...

598
00:42:28,422 --> 00:42:30,632
- ...that fans would recognize it.
- Right.

599
00:42:32,134 --> 00:42:37,264
It's obviously the scene
upon which the whole story turns.

600
00:42:37,431 --> 00:42:39,057
He's got my money!

601
00:42:39,266 --> 00:42:40,892
Thanks.

602
00:42:41,893 --> 00:42:44,646
What the hell's the matter with you?
You let him go!

603
00:42:45,647 --> 00:42:49,151
Look at the rake to this ceiling.
That's what I was referring to...

604
00:42:49,317 --> 00:42:52,154
...when I mentioned Neil designed this
to seem like...

605
00:42:52,320 --> 00:42:55,073
...it was underneath the stadium.

606
00:42:55,240 --> 00:42:57,242
I love Tobey's face here.

607
00:42:57,409 --> 00:43:00,328
He's a sinner.
He's let pride and anger rule.

608
00:43:00,495 --> 00:43:03,832
You won't see that look
anywhere else in the picture.

609
00:43:03,999 --> 00:43:10,088
He's full of himself, feels his own
bitter justice has been served.

610
00:43:10,255 --> 00:43:12,507
The guy deserved it.

611
00:43:15,135 --> 00:43:20,140
It's a sin he'll end up paying for
the rest of his life.

612
00:43:22,809 --> 00:43:25,645
- What happened?
- Someone got hurt.

613
00:43:28,023 --> 00:43:31,193
- Excuse me. Excuse me. Excuse me.
- Stay back.

614
00:43:31,693 --> 00:43:33,528
- Stay back!
- That's my uncle!

615
00:43:35,697 --> 00:43:38,325
- What happened?
- Carjacker. He's been shot.

616
00:43:38,492 --> 00:43:42,037
We just called the paramedics.
They're on their way.

617
00:43:42,204 --> 00:43:43,622
Uncle Ben?

618
00:43:44,164 --> 00:43:46,833
Cliff Robertson was a real sport
in shooting this.

619
00:43:47,000 --> 00:43:50,128
It's probably 3:00 in the morning,
it was freezing cold...

620
00:43:50,295 --> 00:43:53,006
...and we'd say,
"Get Cliff on the ground."

621
00:43:53,173 --> 00:43:56,676
He'd just throw himself right
down on the cold concrete.

622
00:43:56,885 --> 00:43:59,721
No screaming for a furni-pad
or any of that nonsense.

623
00:43:59,888 --> 00:44:05,352
He'd throw himself down and
wait for the camera crew to set up.

624
00:44:05,519 --> 00:44:07,938
He's a real professional.

625
00:44:15,862 --> 00:44:21,243
It was written originally
that Cliff was already expired...

626
00:44:21,409 --> 00:44:23,829
...when Tobey's character
came up to him.

627
00:44:23,995 --> 00:44:27,916
It was his idea. He said,
"Why don't we just have me alive...

628
00:44:28,083 --> 00:44:32,546
...to make contact with Peter
one last time?" It's a great idea.

629
00:44:35,674 --> 00:44:40,595
That alley he just ran in was the same
alley that he climbed up the wall in.

630
00:44:40,762 --> 00:44:44,474
We shot one in the day
and this at night, obviously.

631
00:44:45,267 --> 00:44:47,269
Downtown Los Angeles.

632
00:44:49,187 --> 00:44:51,690
- I love this.
- I have a funny story about this.

633
00:44:51,857 --> 00:44:57,863
We did a test of CG Spidey
climbing up the wall...

634
00:44:58,029 --> 00:45:03,451
...which was a very early iteration
of this scene right here.

635
00:45:04,035 --> 00:45:07,789
I took the test, I called Amy Pascal
and John Calley and I said:

636
00:45:07,956 --> 00:45:12,294
"We put Tobey in the suit and we
tested him climbing up.

637
00:45:12,502 --> 00:45:15,630
We put a wall on its side
and tested him climbing up the wall."

638
00:45:15,797 --> 00:45:19,467
We were in pre-production. I was
trying to get more money for the movie.

639
00:45:19,634 --> 00:45:23,597
I called them into the screening room
and they came down and watched it.

640
00:45:23,763 --> 00:45:27,809
It was CG, but I said it was Tobey
in the suit. They went nuts.

641
00:45:27,976 --> 00:45:31,146
They said, "Oh, my God, it's amazing!
He looks so incredible"

642
00:45:31,646 --> 00:45:33,732
Then we laughed.

643
00:45:34,649 --> 00:45:39,279
This was a composite of Tobey's real
face put into the CGI Spider-Man.

644
00:45:39,446 --> 00:45:41,531
That was a very tricky move.

645
00:45:56,463 --> 00:46:00,967
I enjoy watching him struggling with
swinging. He's never done it before.

646
00:46:01,134 --> 00:46:04,471
I love the subtlety that you
and John Dykstra put together in here...

647
00:46:04,638 --> 00:46:07,182
...of him twisting and turning
on one of these shots...

648
00:46:07,349 --> 00:46:11,061
...showing him struggling
with his gift and curse.

649
00:46:11,853 --> 00:46:14,940
Arthur Coburn, was insistent,
one of my editors...

650
00:46:15,148 --> 00:46:20,946
...that we had to track his progression,
as far as his development of grace.

651
00:46:21,112 --> 00:46:25,533
He had to be as awkward as possible
in this early sequence to sell it.

652
00:46:25,700 --> 00:46:28,370
- And I thought that was a great idea.
- Yeah, it was.

653
00:46:37,003 --> 00:46:39,506
I shot this sequence
with our second unit...

654
00:46:39,673 --> 00:46:42,092
...director of photography,
Chris Faloona.

655
00:46:45,345 --> 00:46:49,599
He did a lot of great second unit work
for us. Chris is a garner.

656
00:46:49,808 --> 00:46:52,143
So happy to be going with him.

657
00:47:09,995 --> 00:47:13,164
This is a beautiful set built by Neil.

658
00:47:16,418 --> 00:47:21,673
It's supposed to be the interior
of the abandoned part...

659
00:47:21,840 --> 00:47:24,426
...of the New York
Port Authority Building.

660
00:47:24,676 --> 00:47:28,263
Where the old ferry
used to arrive every day.

661
00:47:32,267 --> 00:47:33,601
Who's there?

662
00:47:59,878 --> 00:48:02,964
Don't hurt me. Give me a chance.
Give me a chance!

663
00:48:03,173 --> 00:48:07,635
What about my uncle?
Did you give him a chance? Did you?

664
00:48:07,802 --> 00:48:09,304
Answer me!

665
00:48:12,682 --> 00:48:13,975
<i>Stop that guy!</i>

666
00:48:17,312 --> 00:48:20,106
- Great moment.
- It's very powerful.

667
00:48:20,482 --> 00:48:23,985
Again, this moment
is so much a trigger...

668
00:48:24,194 --> 00:48:30,450
...and so integral to what made
the whole story work in the comic book.

669
00:48:30,617 --> 00:48:36,081
There's this whole notion that
Spider-Man doesn't ever kill anybody.

670
00:48:36,247 --> 00:48:41,169
But he has to be responsible for this
guy's death, so the guy actually trips.

671
00:48:41,336 --> 00:48:47,217
But the whole, sort of,
ethic of Spider-Man is...

672
00:48:47,425 --> 00:48:51,846
- ...he defends people, but he doesn't...
- Kill them.

673
00:48:52,597 --> 00:48:57,310
Even, of course, with the Goblin,
who's responsible for his own death.

674
00:48:58,937 --> 00:49:02,315
He just has a lot of good luck
in that way.

675
00:49:13,118 --> 00:49:15,495
This was an image that we loved.

676
00:49:15,662 --> 00:49:19,124
Which was also an early image
Sam had...

677
00:49:19,290 --> 00:49:22,877
...of Peter on one of the eagles
in the Chrysler Building.

678
00:49:23,044 --> 00:49:27,382
If you know New York, you'll know that
skyline is something that we made up...

679
00:49:27,549 --> 00:49:30,218
...which was something we did often
in the movie.

680
00:49:30,385 --> 00:49:36,391
We took architecture that we liked and
manipulated it in the CG world.

681
00:49:36,558 --> 00:49:42,063
So you know it's New York,
