820
00:59:07,962 --> 00:59:09,255
I won't.

821
00:59:11,424 --> 00:59:13,134
I won't tell Harry.

822
00:59:19,098 --> 00:59:22,977
I love that location,
it's right across from NYU.

823
00:59:23,144 --> 00:59:26,313
It was an amazing apartment,
where the exterior was shot.

824
00:59:26,480 --> 00:59:31,110
- This was a set that Neil designed.
- Yeah, this is an amazing apartment.

825
00:59:31,277 --> 00:59:34,488
Where do you get this apartment
in New York? I'd love to live here.

826
00:59:34,655 --> 00:59:36,824
Daddy got it for him. Daddy.

827
00:59:38,492 --> 00:59:40,828
They even have a nice balcony.

828
00:59:42,663 --> 00:59:45,166
I remember when we worked
on this set...

829
00:59:45,374 --> 00:59:49,837
...Tobey had a lot of good notes
for myself and Neil Spisak...

830
00:59:50,004 --> 00:59:55,301
...about the reality of the size of the
loft that these two would really have.

831
00:59:55,468 --> 00:59:58,012
And the style of the furnishings.

832
00:59:58,262 --> 01:00:03,392
He had a more realistic take and guided
us from a character point of view...

833
01:00:03,601 --> 01:00:06,020
...which is so important
in making a picture...

834
01:00:06,187 --> 01:00:11,108
...to listen to actors and believe they
have the best take on who they are...

835
01:00:11,275 --> 01:00:15,446
...and what they know about
their world, to listen to that.

836
01:00:18,908 --> 01:00:23,204
See I love this intrigue,
this set up of the triangle.

837
01:00:23,412 --> 01:00:25,456
Sam had said, even early on...

838
01:00:25,623 --> 01:00:31,003
<i>"mat he wanted 'Ms 90210 or Melrose
Place... I don't watch those shows.</i>

839
01:00:31,170 --> 01:00:32,338
Very soap Opera-Y-

